transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir, I was calling to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: I can get online here, but I don't find a way to cancel it.

Speaker 2: Right. I got Ron Eckerman in Caldwell, Texas, or excuse me, Kansas.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: All right. Yeah, the cancellation button isn't on the website anywhere,

Speaker 1: because if you accidentally press it, it's a whole discrepancy thing.

Speaker 2: We've got to reorder the prescription and whatnot,

Speaker 1: so we'd rather just have everybody call in and request anything over the phone

Speaker 2: with one of us.

Speaker 1: With your situation, do you just not need any type of refills at the moment?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: I had some from my last one.

Speaker 2: I received them, and then I just got this order, so I have money.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me reverse that, and then what I'll do,

Speaker 2: I'll postpone any future one from now until June.

Speaker 1: That way you've got some time to kill what you've got and call in

Speaker 2: and request it if you need it a little bit earlier,

Speaker 1: and they won't come as often as they have been.

Speaker 2: It'll be like whenever you need it at that point as well, all right?

Speaker 1: Perfect.

Speaker 2: All right. Sounds good. Let me do that.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Okay. Everything's done.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right, Ron. Hope you have a great rest of your day, all right?

Speaker 1: You too. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye-bye.
